            <title><![CDATA[HIJACKED!]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[<img src="https://imgflo.herokuapp.com/graph/2b2431f8e7ba7b0/06543e9fb52d54d5ee60e4d4f903cdcc/croprotate.png?cropheight=561&cropwidth=990&degrees=0&input=https%3A%2F%2Fthe-grid-user-content.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com%2F31311477-b8bb-4d5b-aa59-571422446083.png&x=4&y=0" title="HIJACKED!" alt="Our Limbic System&rsquo;s response to both the &quot;innocent&quot; foods and the street drugs pictured above is the same: It floods our brain with dopamine. Yet two of these are shown to our children in TV commercials">,<h1>HIJACKED!</h1>,<h3><strong>Despite her entering the weight-loss industry, NISOD Excellence Award professor, double PhD (Brain &amp; Cognitive Sciences) &amp; Berkeley summa cum laude, Dr. Susan Peirce’s video is irrefutable: Form, rather than “Substance” lurks behind all addictive foods</strong></h3>,<p><strong>CEREBRAL (SOFTWARE): </strong>2 of the substances pictured here are everyday foods, the other 2 are street drugs. All 4 cause dopamine-spike responses from the <a href="https://www.reference.com/science/limbic-system-39014f3c7323b28c?qo=cdpArticles">Limbic System</a> that hijack our <a href="https://www.reference.com/science/prefrontal-cortex-3a271896b743339b">Pre-frontal Cortex</a>’s ability to think. This part of <a href="http://susanpeircethompson.com/about-susan/">Dr. Peirce’s video</a>, starts on minute 35:00, yet <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J5YvefCIqHk">all of it is worth watching</a></p>]]></description>
